The paper proposes a new method for extracting principal components of multi-way data using tensor singular value decomposition. The applications mentioned in the paper are related to computer vision and image processing, indicating that the paper is likely to belong to the computer science sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and information theory (cs.IT). The method also involves iterative thresholding, which suggests that it may be relevant to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and signal processing (cs.SI).
